## 1. Migration

- [ ] 1.1 Create migration `AddHmacKeyToAccounts` — add `hmac_key` column as `:binary`, nullable initially
- [ ] 1.2 Backfill existing accounts with `:crypto.strong_rand_bytes(32)` via `execute/1` or `Repo` calls in migration
- [ ] 1.3 Alter column to `null: false` after backfill

## 2. Schema Update

- [ ] 2.1 Add `field :hmac_key, :binary, redact: true` to `GA.Accounts.Account` schema
- [ ] 2.2 Ensure `hmac_key` is NOT in the `cast/3` permitted fields — it is never set from external input
- [ ] 2.3 Derive `Inspect` protocol or use `redact: true` to hide key from logs and IEx

## 3. Key Generation and Retrieval

- [ ] 3.1 Update `GA.Accounts.create_account/2` to generate `hmac_key` via `:crypto.strong_rand_bytes(32)` and `put_change` it onto the changeset before insert
